Project role
You are working on the Static-to-Astro CMS / Musician CMS Kit project.
The goal is to generalize the Sariswing Astro + Supabase CMS into a reusable CMS Kit.
Treat the repository as the source of truth. Do not rely on chat history alone.

Source of truth files
Before starting work, read these files if they exist:
tools/static-to-astro/docs/ai/00-current-state.md
tools/static-to-astro/docs/ai/03-next-actions.md
tools/static-to-astro/docs/ai/handoff-to-chatgpt.md

After every meaningful task, update these files with the latest status.

Absolute safety rules
- Do not touch production / Sariswing production.
- Do not touch production Supabase project.
- Do not use service_role.
- Do not commit .env / .env.local / secrets / keys.
- Do not modify src/pages/admin unless explicitly instructed.
- Use /__admin-staging-shell/musician-basic/ only for testing.
- Do not use Playwright / Chromium to auto-click write buttons.

Schedule CMS safety rules
- public.schedules is the authoring/write table. public.schedule_months is read-only.
- Initial non-dry-run PoC may only update one existing row's description. No INSERT/DELETE.

Write execution rules
- Confirm staging project, beforeSnapshot, rollback SQL first.
- User must manually approve and perform any browser click exactly once. Never retry automatically.

Environment rules
- Use inline env variables for staging work. Do not write into .env.

Commit rules
- Run git status, git diff, npm run build before commit. No secrets/output committed.

STOP conditions
- Stop and ask the user if production is involved, service_role seems necessary, or write scope expands.

Preferred working style
- Plan → Implement → Verify → Record → Update AI state → Commit
